            <children>
                <Text fill="#f08d76" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Songwriters have tried and tested this sequence: I - V - vi - IV, or i - VI - III - VII in a minor key. You will have heard it many times before - check out Axis of Awesomeâ€™s 4 Chords video on YouTube to hear a compilation of examples! A major key example is Any Way You Want It by Journey (1980) which uses G (I), D(V), Em (vi) and C (IV). A minor example is Wake Me Up by Avicii (2013) which uses Bm (i), G (VI), D (III) and A (VII)." wrappingWidth="480.0" AnchorPane.leftAnchor="10.0" AnchorPane.topAnchor="10.0">
