                <Text fill="#f08d76" layoutX="20.0" layoutY="32.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="A cool thing about this sequence is that in a major key, it comprises of the same 4 chords as the relative minor. For example, in C major the sequence is C (I), G (V), Am (vi), F (IV) and in the relative minor, A minor, the sequence is Am (i), F (VI), C (III), G (VII). Have a listen to Mirrors by Justin Timberlake (2013) which uses this to create modal ambiguity and transition between major and minor from chorus to verse." wrappingWidth="480.0" AnchorPane.bottomAnchor="50.0" AnchorPane.leftAnchor="10.0">
